  How to Apply These Terms to Your New Programs

   If you develop a new program and you want it to be of the kind
that can be shared and changed by everyone, the best way to do that
is to apply the GNU General Public License to it.

   To do this, you need to keep the license notice intact and add
the appropriate notices for any copyright holders of the program
you are developing, so they know how they can benefit from it.

   Also, you should give everyone the right to share and change
the software that you create.  This is essential to keeping the
program free and usable.

   If someone else develops software using your program or any
copyrighted portions of it, they also need to follow the same rules
you did, so it is strongly recommended that you include this
type of license.

   The internationally recognized GPLv3 is a perfect fit for
this type of program, and it’s a great way to give everyone equal
opportunity in technology development, including giving you the
ultimate rights over any software you write.

